

The Nepali government has constituted a peace fund to generate resources from internal and external assistance to move ahead the ongoing peace process in the country, local Kantipur daily reported on Friday.

"The meeting of Council of Ministers on Tuesday decided in this regard," the daily reported referring to an official at the Ministry of Finance.

"The government needs 85,714 million U.S. dollars immediately, the source said."We aim to generate that much amount through the peace fund," the official added.

As per plan, the works including physical infrastructure development, election to constituent assembly, rehabilitation, employment and security of displaced people will be carried out through this fund.

"We are planning to request internal and external donors soon to assist for the fund," the official said.

The government has put 1.4 million dollars as seed money in the fund.

